Two new films topped the domestic box office on their opening night Friday. “Uncharted” — a treasure-hunt flick based on a video game — raked in $15.4 million in its premiere, according to IMDB’s Box Office Mojo database. Road-trip comedy “Dog” came next with $5 million on its opening night. Whodunit “Death on the Nile,” last week’s leader, grossed $1.8 million on Friday, or $20.5 million cumulatively.